	<div class="ibox-image"><a href="./File:Chinese-grammar-wiki－keyi.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Chinese-grammar-wiki－keyi.jpg" src="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/8/87/Chinese-grammar-wiki%EF%BC%8Dkeyi.jpg/300px-Chinese-grammar-wiki%EF%BC%8Dkeyi.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/8/87/Chinese-grammar-wiki%EF%BC%8Dkeyi.jpg/450px-Chinese-grammar-wiki%EF%BC%8Dkeyi.jpg 1.5x, https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/8/87/Chinese-grammar-wiki%EF%BC%8Dkeyi.jpg/600px-Chinese-grammar-wiki%EF%BC%8Dkeyi.jpg 2x" /></a></div>
</div> 
<p>可以 (kěyǐ) is an <a href="Auxiliary_verb" title="Auxiliary verb">auxiliary verb</a> primarily used for expressing permission. It's often translated as "can," but in order to not get it confused with other words, it's best to think of it as "may" to emphasize the <i>permission</i> aspect.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2>Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
